org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.fx.viewer

Class FXViewer

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.viewer.AbstractViewer<javafx.scene.Node>
      • org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.fx.viewer.FXViewer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IActivatable, IAdaptable, IAdaptable.Bound<IDomain<javafx.scene.Node>>, IDisposable, IViewer<javafx.scene.Node>

    public class FXViewer
extends AbstractViewer<javafx.scene.Node>
    The FXViewer is an AbstractViewer that is parameterized by Node. It manages an InfiniteCanvas that displays the viewer's contents, adds scrollbars when necessary, and renders a background grid.

      • viewerFocusedProperty

        public javafx.beans.property.ReadOnlyBooleanProperty viewerFocusedProperty()
        Description copied from interface: IViewer
        Returns a ReadOnlyBooleanProperty that represents the "focused" state of this IViewer. An IViewer is focused when its visualization has keyboard focus and its window is active, i.e. it is focused if it will receive keyboard events.
